author: Ben Shapiro
description:
Ben discusses the system of checks and balances within democratic republics. One of the checks and balances initially was impeachment, and Ben details Alexander Hamilton’s initial requirements for what qualifies for an impeachment. He also talks about the constitutional crises that come with setting up fake “objective” legal enforcement bodies. Ben also discusses President Lula da Silva openly consolidating power in the executive branch in anti-democratic ways, outlining why administrative states don’t work.
